{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}Scroll area · Stisla{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>Scroll area</h1>
    <p class="lead">An overflowed region with a custom scrollbar that overlays without taking layout space.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic</h2>
    <p>Drop <code>.scroll-area</code> on any bounded element and tag it with <code>data-stisla-scroll-area</code>. The native scrollbar disappears; the overlay bar fades in on hover and while scrolling.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="scroll-area scroll-area--bordered" data-stisla-scroll-area style="height: 16rem;">
      <div style="padding: 1rem;">
        <h3 class="m-0 mb-2 fs-4 fw-semibold">Release notes</h3>
        <p>The new token system retunes every component from a single root override. Brand color, radius, spacing, shadow, dark mode. One file, no per-component tweaks. The cascade picks the change up wherever the override lands.</p>
        <p>State derivation moved off Sass color math and onto runtime <code>color-mix(in oklch, ...)</code>. Hover and active percentages live next to the component, where reviewers can see them.</p>
        <p>BEM stays for static structure. Runtime state splits two ways. <code>[data-state]</code> for concepts that mainstream primitive libraries also surface, <code>.is-*</code> for everything else. Same CSS, every implementation.</p>
        <p>Forms got the long-promised reset. Inputs, selects, textareas and switches all read from one shared field-row partial. The <code>.field</code> family wraps label, control, help and error in a single block with consistent spacing.</p>
        <p>Sidebar collapses to icon-only with a single class flip. App-shell handles the full layout: pinned navbar, scrolling sidebar, content area that respects safe-area insets on mobile Safari.</p>
        <p>Dialog, drawer, dropdown and popover share the same focus-trap and scroll-lock plumbing. Backdrops are <code>inert</code> so screen readers skip them. Reduced-motion users get instant open and close, no animation.</p>
        <p>Toast lives at the top level. Stack from any corner. Auto-dismiss with a hover pause, swipe to dismiss on touch, programmatic <code>toast()</code> helper for one-liners from anywhere in your app.</p>
        <p>Carousel runs on Embla. Slides, controls, indicators, captions, autoplay. Optional bundle, so dashboards that don't need it don't pay for it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Installation</h2>
    <p>Skip this step if you're on the <code>stisla-full</code> bundle, it already ships with Scroll area. On the core <code>stisla</code> bundle, add it alongside as a script tag or via your package manager.</p>

    <div class="tabs mt-4" data-stisla-tabs>
      <div class="tabs__list">
        <button class="tabs__trigger" data-value="compiled">Compiled</button>
        <button class="tabs__trigger" data-value="manual">Manual</button>
      </div>

      <div class="tabs__panel" data-value="compiled">
        <p>Add the component's stylesheet and script next to the ones loading the core bundle.</p>
        {% call ui.code(lang='html') %}
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@stisla/css@beta/dist/components/scroll-area.css">
        <script type="module" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@stisla/vanilla@beta/dist/components/scroll-area.js"></script>
        {% endcall %}
        <p>The script auto-registers on the global <code>Stisla</code> instance, so no extra wiring is needed.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tabs__panel" data-value="manual">
        <p>Import the CSS and the JS. Both files register themselves on load, so no manual <code>register()</code> or <code>Stisla.init()</code> call is needed.</p>
        {% call ui.code(lang='js') %}
        import '@stisla/css/components/scroll-area';
        import '@stisla/vanilla/components/scroll-area';
        {% endcall %}
        <p>OverlayScrollbars rides along as a transitive dependency of <code>@stisla/vanilla</code>, so no extra install is needed.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Horizontal</h2>
    <p>Set <code>overflow-y</code> to <code>hidden</code> for a track that scrolls along the x axis only. The card row stays one row at any width.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="scroll-area scroll-area--bordered" data-stisla-scroll-area data-stisla-scroll-area-overflow-y="hidden">
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 1rem; min-width: max-content;">
        <div class="card m-0" style="min-width: 14rem;"><div class="card__body"><strong>Acme Inc</strong><div class="text-muted-foreground fs-2">Active project</div></div></div>
        <div class="card m-0" style="min-width: 14rem;"><div class="card__body"><strong>Helix Health</strong><div class="text-muted-foreground fs-2">Active project</div></div></div>
        <div class="card m-0" style="min-width: 14rem;"><div class="card__body"><strong>Northwind Labs</strong><div class="text-muted-foreground fs-2">Active project</div></div></div>
        <div class="card m-0" style="min-width: 14rem;"><div class="card__body"><strong>Forge &amp; Tide</strong><div class="text-muted-foreground fs-2">Paused</div></div></div>
        <div class="card m-0" style="min-width: 14rem;"><div class="card__body"><strong>Quill Press</strong><div class="text-muted-foreground fs-2">Active project</div></div></div>
        <div class="card m-0" style="min-width: 14rem;"><div class="card__body"><strong>Mariner Logistics</strong><div class="text-muted-foreground fs-2">Archived</div></div></div>
        <div class="card m-0" style="min-width: 14rem;"><div class="card__body"><strong>Oryx Systems</strong><div class="text-muted-foreground fs-2">Active project</div></div></div>
